<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n09021e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09021e">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09021e"> 21(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> exaggerated pop</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><b>City and District News &hellip; Exaggerated Claims</b>.&mdash;Charles Waters, before the Recorder, claimed &pound;124 4&frasl;11 for men&apos;s suits and women&apos;s wear seized by armed men in his house at Rathgar avenue. The Recorder asked if the applicant was a native of this country, Applicant said he was not. Mr. Webb (Messrs. Webb and Webb), for the applicant, said he had been 30 years in business in this country and became a naturalised subject as soon as he possibly could. Waters was a translation of his original name. The Recorder, remarking that he would put an end to <mark>exaggerated</mark> claims, allowed &pound;25. <small> <a name="FJ21feb24" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#FJ21feb24"><cite title="source">Freeman's Journal</cite></a> (21 February 1924) 7/3</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
